  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whosoever toucheth them shall be holy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] This does not mean that only priests who have properly purified themselves may touch the most holy things, but that anyone, priest or layman, who inadvertently comes in contact with anything that is ‘most holy,’ becomes holy (i.e. dedicated to God, and put at His disposal), cp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 6:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 7:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". No rule is given here about the treatment of such persons; for inanimate things which are brought into contact with the ‘most holy,’ see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Leviticus 6:27-28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 6:27-28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". According to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Haggai 2:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the garment in which ‘holy flesh’ is carried, does not communicate holiness to the food which it may happen to touch.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
